(15, 2, 5, '<h1>Final Project Bachelor Psychology & Technology</h1>\n<h2>Content</h2>\n<p>In a condensed way the student performs a study that covers the whole empirical research cycle of developing a specific research question, using theory in order to answer the question and testing the theory by the collection of data. Knowledge from various disciplines is integrated and students practice in performing research on a technology related problem. This will be linked to the technical specializations in the BSc and the Master HTI: Robotics, Living and ICT. </p>\n<p>Students can collaborate in groups for literature search or the collection of data. However, they have to formulate a specific question to be answered by their Bachelor Thesis that is written individually.</p>\n\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>In order to get permission to take part, you need to have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>obtained the P-diploma</li>\n<li>passed the courses 0HV00 and 0HV50 at the time of registration (0HV110 is also recommended)</li>\n<li>90 ECTS two quartile before the actual start of the Bachelor end project</li>\n<p>N.B. students who may have study delay because of this regulation can contact Monique Jansen-Vullers.</p>\n\n<p>For more infmoration, see the 0BEPP0 course information.</p>\n', 'en', '2017-04-04 13:12:06', '2017-04-04 13:09:54'),
